President Obama has nominated Abid Riaz Qureshi to serve on the United States District Court for the District of Columbia. Qureshi is a partner at the law firm Latham & Watkins LLP, specializing in cases involving the False Claims Act, health care fraud, and securities violations. He has been with the firm for his entire legal career, currently serving as the Global Chair of the Pro Bono Committee. Qureshi has also held positions such as Co-Chair of the Litigation Department and member of the District of Columbia Bar Associationâ€™s Legal Ethics Committee. He graduated with a J.D. cum laude from Harvard Law School in 1997 and a B.A. summa cum laude from Cornell University in 1993.